Upgraded to Intellij 2016. Using Tomcat 8 and Java 8 Eliminated some hibernate dependencies and cleaned up artifacts Added Jersey RESTful framework and handle requests in /rest/MathspringService.
Added Child assent stuff
Added a new method to the MARI service for checking how many problems a student can work on in a standard
Added Pair class
Added Pair class
Added more rules and conditions to support messages that happen at BeginProblem events.
Added built-in pretests at login time.
Added Posttest and javascript form validation of pre/post test questions.

All pretest and posttest features working including warning messages about taking too long, progress bars and dynamically added buttons. This means that authoring a problem needs to have a waitTime (in seconds) to tell the system how long to wait until popping up a message. For many questions there is no correct answer. For those questions that are math and short answer is the type of the input, we can really only do a simple string comparison

added grading of pretest problems. If the answer field of the question is non-null, it will do a string match to see if the user-input matches the correct answer (note that we DO NOT USE a,b,c for multi-choice answers - it will be the actual text string that sits next to the radio button)
Made images for pretests come from blobs in the db. This meant adding a ImageFetchServlet to get them.
Made pretest problem have a -1 waitTime if its null in the db and then eliminate the popup dialogs if this is the value for the question.
Trying to fix layout problems in quickAuth
Working AffectivaService with jersey 1.9. Cannot get jersey 2.3 working

Made pretest and posttests login interventions check to see if the test is active before going into it. This will allow me to turn off all old pretests so that classes that reference them will not try to run them.
Fixed class creation in the teacher tools. Pages were set with &teacherId hidden input instead of teacherId which keeps track of the teacherId in all the pages.
Added longAnswer pretest question type

Fixed problem with LoginInterventionInput events not going back to their intervention selector correctly. Now use the LoginSequence to find the correct selector and instantiate it so that its config.xml is set ..
fixed bugs in pre/post tests. It was not giving the first prolem and it wasn't showing long answer inputs. It was not putting seqNum and timeOnProblem in the db.

Added LC Rule Command XMLLCRule for better reloading of XML into db and listing the rules. Added new rules and rulesets. There is now one rule file lcrules.xml and three ruleset files that just put rules into sets. I added caching to the InferenceEngine so that on one cycle it will store each value for each function that runs in a condition. This should speed up the engine a bit.
Teacher delete bug fix.
Changed the AskEmotion stuff to pose 4 questions of user and put them in the db. Also added -rs arg to XMLLCRule so it will print either a ruleset or all rules.
Teacher delete bug fix.
meta rule override not being saved/used in db bug fix.

Fulfill request to allow img tags in the answers of pretest questions.
This meant doing something different in the grading of multi-choice questions and sending back the letter of the choice if there is an image in there.

Fixed bugs in the Learning Companions so that they don't return multiple video clips and they complete their logic rather than relying on the super classes to return idle clips.
Also fixes a bug in the AskEmotionIS to reset the timer when the user answers the dialog rather than when it is presented.
